<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/25> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7418> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7418" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 35. Tr. pl. 43. His tribunate, like that of Agrippa, depends on Niccolini's view (FTP 355) that they were tribunes when Cornificius prosecuted Brutus and Agrippa Cassius. This is improbable, since the actions were apparently taken before a quaestio. See below, on Agrippa. Consul 35. In MRR 2.406, refer also to ILLRP 1271b.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6480> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6480" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Africa, he celebrated a triumph ex Africa on December 3 (Fast. Barb., Degrassi 342f., 570, without the number of the year). He rebuilt the temple of Diana on the Aventine (Suet. Aug. 29.5; cf. CIL 6.4305-ILS 1732; and see Shipley, MAAR 9 [1931] 30-32). See PIR² 2.373, no. 1503; De Laet no. 151; and above, on Claudius Pulcher." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6467> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6467" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Africa (see 34, and 32, Promagistrates). See PIR² 2.373, no. 1503; De Laet no. 151." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6440> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6440" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Succeeded T. Statilius Taurus in Africa, almost certainly as Proconsul (see 33, Promagistrates). See PIR² 2.373, no. 1503; De Laet no. 15 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6399> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6399" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "BCH 54 (1930) 490f.; names supplied in SC de, Aphrodisiensibus (Viereck, Sermo Graec. p. VII, and addenda to no. 19, p. 40)\" office-xref=\"; Fast. Mag. Vic., Degrassi 283, 288; ibid. 136, 508f.; Dio, 49, Index, and 18.6, and 33.1; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Cornificiums, NS 1933, 331, no. 421; on Pompeius, see D.-G. 4.324, no. 18; on Cornificius, PIR² 2.373, no. 1503; Do Laet no. 151." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6387> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6387" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate under Octavian (Vell. 2.79.4) in command of the three legions which landed at Tauromenium and were cut off. He saved them by means of a hazardous march to Agrippa near Mylae (App. BC 5.111-115; Dio 49.5-7; cf. Vell. 2.79.4). See PIR² 2.373, no. 1503; De Laet no. 15 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6336> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6336" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. Commander of a fleet under Octavian (probably a Legate; see 36, Legates), he brought a fleet from Ravenna to Tarentum (App. BC 5.80), and in the naval battle at the Sicilian straits rammed the flagship of Sextus Pompey's Lieutenant Demochares (App. BC 5.86; cf. Liv. Per. 128; see above, Triumviri R. P. C., on Octavian). See PIR² 2.373, no. 1503; De Laet no. 151." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6047> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6047" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The accuser of Brutus in the trials instituted under the Lex Pedia (see above, Consuls; Plut. Brut. 27.3-5; cf. Vell. 2.69.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10054> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10054" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Africa. MRR II.419, Itgenshorst no. 286 (33/32), Rich no. 287 (33)." .
